directions: Bathroom is located behind the wall that displays flowers.  Walk up the ramp and to your right.
comment: Daily, 9 am - 10 pm

name: Sheetz
directions: Back right-hand side of the store. Locking genderfree stall squeezed between two traditional bathrooms.
comment: Open 24-7. Very clean!

name: adar kosher pizza
directions: single bathroom in the kitchen

comment: two separate bathrooms in one sructure its an outhouse

name: capriotti's sandwich shop
directions: locking bathrooms in rear of the store

name: Hilton
directions: 6th Floor Brisbane Qld Australia
comment: Nice and clean, always empty, enter through foyer

name: Easton Town Center
directions: There is a family bathroom in the back hallway on the east side of the main mall building, near Shadowbox and the Easton offices.  It is single-stall, locking, and accessible during all hours of business.

name: Grove City College Student Union
directions: First floor has two gender-neutral bathrooms.  Second floor has single-gender restrooms.
comment: Open 24 hours except for Saturday night.Student union is open to everyone.

name: Gay and Lesbian Center
directions: rear of center ask to use the bathroom
comment: mon-fri 11 am to 7 pm

name: lowe's
directions: front of storeby men's and women's rooms
comment: 7 days a week

name: mcdonald's
directions: east side of store ask clerk to open restroom

name: rainbow laundromat
directions: back of laundromat ask clerk for key restroom for customers only
comment: 7 days a week

name: venetian hotel casino
directions: casino level past box office walk down steps into venetian congress center
comment: 24 hours

name: Green Valley Grocery
directions: back of store ask clerk for the key

name: wal-mart neighborhood market
directions: west side of store by mans and women's rooms
comment: 24 hours

name: wynn hotel and casino
directions: next to box office
comment: 24 hours

name: wal-mart supercenter
directions: rear of the store
comment: 24 hours

name: Golden Gate Bridge
directions: Outside of the fort at the base of the golden gate bridge is a bathroom with three, options male, female and family.

name: Baker Beach
directions: at the end of the parking lot are several portable toilets. One is wheelchair accessible
comment: san francisco's very own nude beach

name: Ocean Beach
directions: Along the parking lot there is usually a portable toilet

name: Salvation Cafe
directions: Near the back of the right-hand half of the restaurant, beyond the bar.
comment: Two separate room bathrooms with purposely ambiguous signs on the door. Both are genderfree/unisex, and it's fun to see straight people contemplate the "signs" on the bathroom while trying to figure out which one they "should" use. This is a funky queer-friendly restaurant, though you will probably need to eat or drink there to use the bathrooms.

name: Barnes & Noble Clybourn
directions: 1st floor in the back, past the newsstand.
comment: The upstairs bathrooms are gendered, but the first floor has a single handicap-accessible one.

name: Conway Laundrymat
directions: headed north, turn right into Post Office parking lot before Cumberland Farms Gas and convienence store. Laudrymat is on your left
comment: Open during hours of operation early in the morning to 10:30 PM. Bathroom is a non gender specific single stall lockable facility on the emmediate right as you walk in the door.

name: The Penguin
directions: walk in & turn right! it's a small place
comment: eat some food, too; it's good and cheap!

name: Pahrump Nugget
directions: Down hall by coffee shop and food court area.
comment: Unisex/family between usual gendered restrooms.

name: Crossroads Mall
directions: Second floor, rear of food court.
comment: Unisex/family along with the usual gendered restrooms.

name: Desert Passage Mall
directions: Scattered about the property.
comment: There are various unisex/family restrooms near some of the usual gendered rooms.

name: Don H. Bottum University Center
directions: This bathroom is on the first floor near the Radio X studio. If you enter from the doors near the green historical sign, just go straight a little bit, and to your left you should see a bathroom.
comment: The University Center is generally open during business hours and possibly a bit longer, with the exception of holidays such as winter break.Just stroll on in and do your business... you are not at all likely to be noticed, especially if you are college-aged or professor-aged.

name: University of Ottawa (Pharmacy Building)
comment: Go to health counter, and get key.

name: Blue State Coffee
directions: When you walk in the front door, the bathroom is straight ahead (to the opposite wall) and on your right.
comment: This is a coffee shop.  The employees are liberal, mainly Democrats.  When you're hanging out and/or ordering, sometimes they are really accepting and chill while sometimes they are caught off guard and confused if you don't look like a binary-genetic girl or boy.  I've never had an issue with the bathroom though.  The bathroom is closer to the entrance than where most of the employees stand, so you might be able to sneak in without paying, but it's difficult.

name: Arco  gas station
directions: On the Main street, next to the Ming Chinese restaurant. The bathrooms are in the back, behind the counter.
comment: Two bathrooms- both are single use, locking, and gender neutral.

name: The Rail
directions: It's a single room unisex locking bathroom at the far end of the bar by the jukebox.
comment: Not the most clean, but the people are nice.

name: Tucson Mall
directions: Bottom floor, right before entering the Food Court on the 'Arizona Avenue' side (first restaurants you come to is Cozzoli's Pizza on the left hand side)
comment: Monday-Saturday:  	10:00am-9:00pmSunday: 	        11:00am-6:00pm

name: The Fine Grind
directions: To the left, past the counter and back kitchen.
comment: Converted from a house's bathroom (so there's a shower stall in it and everthang).  You could probably get away with just using the bathroom, but it's a small coffee shop, so they'd prefer that you at least buy something.

name: Phoenix Convention Center
directions: West Building of the Phoenix Convention Center on the ground level, near Starbucks, across the lobby from the information booth, between the men's and woman's restroom.
comment: A family restroom, locking single stall.  Clean (at least when I used it on 9/19/07) and roomy.

name: Cafe Twenty Eight
directions: The bathrooms are through the front door, all the way to the back of the building, on the right.
comment: They have wonderful food, wine, and beer there. There are two single stall gender free bathrooms, one of which is wheelchair accessible. Check them out at http://www.cafetwentyeight.com/.

name: Metropolitan Community Church
directions: Have 2 stalls right inside the front door, and another stall right inside the back door.
comment: Available any time the church is open, which is usually Sundays around 10:00 am to 1:00 pm, Wednesdays around 5:30 pm to 8:30 pm, and occasionally other times.

name: City Place Mall
directions: Bottom floor, at the Food Court
comment: There's a sign outside the bathrooms that says that City Place Mall does not discriminate against people based on race, age, gender identity, etc. I'm not sure if there are wheelchair-accessible stalls or not.

name: Cedar Crest College Cressman Library
directions: In the basement of the library building, next to the stairs.
comment: In order to get into the building, you'll need to sign in at the front desk and show any form of picture ID.

name: L'Etage
directions: L'etage is the bar, restaurant and performance space above Beau Monde, the creperie. The bathrooms are just to the left of the entrance, once you get upstairs.
comment: Two gender-free bathrooms that have plaques that say "WC." So sweet! So gender-free.

name: The Big Hunt
directions: One on the first floor, right side, back of building, near kitchen. One on the first floor, left side, back of building. One on the second floor, right next to the bar.
comment: The Big Hunt is a great low-key bar in Dupont Circle.

name: University of Arizona Library
directions: Walk in the main door facing the mall (it's actually the 2nd floor), walk directly back to the bathrooms and it's on your right

name: Target
directions: They have gendered bathrooms near customer service, but a unisex one is available in the pharmacy area.
comment: bathrooms have always been clean so far as I've seen, which is a huge plus;  also I think the mall itself offers "family" bathrooms that are unisex as well...

name: Arden Mall
directions: In the food court on the second floor by Sears.  Two family bathrooms.

name: Subway
directions: Subway is in the middle of the plaza
comment: Bathrooms are in the back of the store, at the end of a hallway. There's a door marked "Restrooms" that closes off the hallway, so which restroom you pick is hidden from the people/employees in the restaurant.

name: Seattle/Tacoma International Airport
directions: At least the S terminals have 'family' bathrooms coded for either gender. The bathrooms are located on either end of the terminal hidden between the big entrances for the male/female bathrooms.
comment: This is an international airport, so there is a lot of traffic. There may be similar facilities in other terminals at the airport, so look for them.

name: SeaTac Airport
directions: At least the S-gates have 'family' bathrooms flagged as gender-free. There may be more in other terminals.
comment: This is an airport, so there is a lot of traffic around. The 'family' bathrooms are located on either end of the terminal satellite, between the entrances for the gendered bathrooms and easy to overlook.

name: The Potter's Rib
directions: If you face the counter, it is at the end of the hallway you see on the right.
comment: 11am-7:30pm Tuesday through SaturdayAlso try the food. It's homemade barbeque and whatnot.

name: Target
directions: Just inside the entrance to the left before you get to the customer service desk.
comment: Single stall "family" restroom.M-Sa: 8:00 a.m.-10:00 p.m.Su: 8:00 a.m.-9:00 p.m.

name: Frites Alors!
street: ave du parc, east side just north of fairmont
directions: at back of building on the left
comment: genderfree washroom at back of store - if vusy, walk thru and act like you're looking for someone, if not you could still probably confidently walk right in

name: Quail Ridge Books
directions: back corner

name: Triangle Town Center
street: Corner of Capital Blvd and Old Wake Forest Rd. Near 540
directions: 2nd floor, upstairs from the food court, just behind the elevators.  There are 2 of them each with an adult toilet, a childs toilet, and a changing table.
comment: Always clean!

name: Caffeine Cafe
directions: Straight to the back and hang a left, two gender neutral, single occupancy bathrooms await!
comment: We're Trans owned and host a couple Trans events.

name: Gilmore Skytrain Station - Taco Del Mar
directions: Across the street from the Gilmore Skytrain Station, fast food place beside Starbucks called Taco Del Mar (inside and on the right). Two washrooms: one labeled female (locked for employees) and the other labeled male/female/accessible (unlocked when I was there).

name: brew ha ha
directions: straight through to the back, two gender free stalls.

name: ten stone
directions: go past the bar and back on the left, in the direction of 21st street. you can go either way around the bar.
comment: good beer, the people are a little uptight but the bathroom's gender free and great in a pinch

name: Bay Cove Human Services
directions: 5th floor, take elevator up then turn left
comment: human services agency where people generally are only there with an appointment, but you shouldn't run into trouble since people also go there to apply for jobs and do trainings and things. it also seems big enough that everyone would just assume you're there for another department.

name: Cafe Colucci
directions: behind the dining area
comment: great Ethiopian food!

name: Mama Buzz Cafe
directions: walk right in the door, you'll see a mural which is also the bathroom door!

name: Middlebush Hall Ground Floor
directions: Middlebush Hall is located on the University of Missouri campus, at the corner of 9th Street and University Avenue.  Parking is metered.  Bathroom is on the ground floor.
comment: Typically, the building is unlocked whenever students are around.  You might have trouble getting there on Sundays, holidays, or in the middle of the night.

name: Lifelong AIDS Alliance
directions: The first door immediately down the hall at the Seneca Building, just past the front desk, ground floor.Mapquest will lose you; come up to it from Madison and the large signs will be more of a clue.  It is the less obvious of the two Lifelong buildings on either side of the Copy Mart.
comment: There are two buildings at Lifelong and while both have bathrooms, I'm only certain of the one in the Seneca building.  The building, which is the main client-focused building, is open from 8:30 to 5:00 every day.  The staff and volunteers are all friendly and will never judge you; the volunteers are expected not to talk about anyone they work with or for.

name: Hunter College
directions: Second floor of the Hunter College North building, right outside OASIS office (room 217).

name: Half Price Books
comment: Hours: Monday-Saturday 10 a.m. - 10 p.m., Sunday 10 a.m.-8 p.m. Extremely queer-friendly staff (and an awesome store all around)

name: University of Louisville, Ekstrom Library
directions: First floor, in back of building in Tuliptree Cafe

name: Epoch
directions: walk through the door & past the counter, they're to your left
comment: 2 big, clean genderfree locking single stall bathrooms.One is labelled \"Heaven\" and the other is labelled \"Hell.\"

name: 29'th St Mall Restrooms
directions: In the main plaza across from the security  station near Borders Bookstore.
comment: Two Family restrooms of a large size.

name: Denver international Airport
directions: In each terminal near the 'mens room' at the center hub - there is a small door simply marked 'toilet'  It is on both sides of the center hub.  The label is on a small placard - you'll miss it if you are not looking.

name: Burger King
directions: there are two single stall, gender neutral bathrooms on the side of the building closest to market
comment: i'm not sure whether you have to buy anything or not, it's a bit of a sketch location, but hey, it's gender neutral!

name: Mallard's
comment: Single stall bathrooms are pink and blue but there is a little sign that says they're gender-neutral, it's a cute touch.  Great local, natural ice cream and vegan coconut ice too!

name: National Hispanic Cultural Center
directions: The building has a few bathrooms, some gender specific, and at least one that is either 'family' or just not designated.It's on the first floor, in a hall near the theaters (not the gallery).

name: Lewis & Clark College
directions: ADA general access: student center, top floor, end of the hall across from the dining hall (there are two sex-specific restrooms, and one sex-blind).Guest access: guests of students living at the college can use nearly any residence hall restroom -- they default to gender-free/sex-blind status. Student ID or student host are needed to access residence hall restrooms, however.

name: Goodberry's Ice Cream
street: Kildaire Farm Dr. and Wrenn Rd.
directions: Outdoor ice cream stand next to Hibernian Pub.
comment: Have to ask for key. It tells me whether I'm passing convincingly because of which key they hand me.

name: Target
directions: As soon as you walk in, the bathrooms are to your right. The first door you come up to is the family bathroom.

name: Seattle-Tacoma Int'l Airport
directions: Several 'family' restrooms located near regular restrooms down by the baggage claim
comment: Not all the restroom locations have a "family" restroom nearby....  but I know at least 2 are on the airport side of the room (not the street side)  So keep looking.

name: Java Jive
street: Corner of KIldaire Farm and Lochmere Dr.
directions: JavaJive is on the left-hand side of the plaza, next to the wine shop. The bathrooms are behind a wall on the right-hand side of the store.
comment: If you're going to try and sneak in (they post "no public restrooms" signs) use the door facing Kildaire Farm Rd, because it's away from the counter and closer to the bathrooms. You'd be best off just buying something if it's not busy.

name: Target
directions: Straight in the front door, hang an immediate left. You're there!

name: Uncommon Grounds
directions: Back of the coffee shop.
comment: Come right in and enjoy. Typically very clean.

name: Burger King
directions: Just East of I-5, exit #631  Right inside front door.
comment: Not the cleanest, but extremely convenient for travelers on I-5Two non sexed single occupant restrooms

name: Starbucks
street: Near sothern end of 6th Ave, between 7th and 8th Streets.
directions: In the back of the store, there are two gender neutral bathrooms.

name: Nooch
directions: In the back of the restaurant, there is a gender neutral bathroom.

name: UMass Amherst - Lederle
directions: LGRT 16th floor, middle hallway on the right
comment: designated "female" but individual locking, available whenever the building is open (which is nearly 24/7).

name: LivinGood
directions: Walk in the front door and you'll see the bathrooms at the far left-hand corner of the restaurant.  No one will say anything if you just walk in.  The food is really good too :)

name: Koffee Kat
directions: It is directly in front of you after you walk in the front door.  The people at the coffee shop are extremely nice too :)

name: The Burger Ranch
directions: Bathroom is located outside. Left hand side while facing building.
comment: Bathroom (clean!) is for customers only. Very nice employees, just ask for the bathroom key once you've bought a soda or food.
